ic data in checkpoints\\n   - Backwards compatibility with existing checkpoints\\n   - Edge cases in condensation logic\\n\\nUse `git diff main...HEAD` to see the actual changes. Provide specific feedback with file:line references.\",\"agentId\":\"a7fb8d7\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_011m6vKUQcfmFT1p2T8EZmb3\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01C4vDCe8TGqQHnH8NNYtd41\",\"uuid\":\"ed97ef89-e26e-418f-8e57-b63b2eaadb2b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T09:44:15.535Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ed97ef89-e26e-418f-8e57-b63b2eaadb2b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-opencode\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T09:44:20.784Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01DrgKaBm9p4bsvjX3yTwa3o\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012nuxPGxs7iJfbaaTWNDEdr\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/requirements/opencode-integration/review-01.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 01\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-02-20\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: APPROVE (with minor suggestions)\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThis review covers the CLI command and setup changes for OpenCode agent integration in the `feat/add-opencode` branch. The changes add full support for OpenCode as a new AI coding agent, including hooks, transcript handling, resume/rewind functionality, and proper integration with the existing checkpoint system.\\n\\nOverall, the implementation is **well-structured and follows established patterns**. The code is consistent with existing Claude Code and Gemini CLI implementations while accommodating OpenCode's unique SQLite-based storage model.\\n\\n## Files Reviewed\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go` - ExportData handling for OpenCode resume/rewind\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/resume.go` - ExportData propagation to agent's WriteSession\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go` - Switch statement updates for OpenCode agent type\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` - OpenCode hooks installation/uninstallation\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` - Export JSON copying during turn-end\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` - OpenCode agent registration\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` - Interface simplification\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go` - OpenCode transcript condensation\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize_test.go` - Test coverage for OpenCode\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n### 1. [lifecycle.go:212-213] Hardcoded export file path construction\\n\\n```go\\nexportSrc := strings.TrimSuffix(transcriptRef, filepath.Ext(transcriptRef)) + \\\".export.json\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Issue:** The export file path construction assumes the plugin writes an `.export.json` file alongside the transcript with the same base name. This is implicitly coupled to the OpenCode plugin's behavior but not documented or validated.\\n\\n**Suggestion:** Add a comment explaining this contract with the plugin, or consider making this an agent interface method so it's explicit:\\n\\n```go\\n// Export JSON is written by the OpenCode plugin alongside the transcript.\\n// Format: <transcript-base>.export.json (e.g., session-123.jsonl -> session-123.export.json)\\nexportSrc := strings.TrimSuffix(transcriptRef, filepath.Ext(transcriptRef)) + \\\".export.json\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### 2. [rewind.go:685-704, 736-755] Duplicated export data handling blocks\\n\\nThe code for handling export data when WriteSession is called appears twice with nearly identical logic (lines 685-704 and 736-755).\\n\\n**Suggestion:** Extract to a helper function to reduce duplication:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc writeSessionWithExportData(agent agentpkg.Agent, sessionID string, content, exportData []byte) error {\\n    sessionFile, err := resolveTranscriptPath(sessionID, agent)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return err\\n    }\\n    if err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(sessionFile), 0o750); err != nil {\\n        return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to create agent session directory: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n    agentSession := &agentpkg.AgentSession{\\n        SessionID:  sessionID,\\n        AgentName:  agent.Name(),\\n        SessionRef: sessionFile,\\n        NativeData: content,\\n        ExportData: exportData,\\n    }\\n    return agent.WriteSession(agentSession)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n### 1. [explain.go:536-541, 1529-1537] Redundant default case after switch\\n\\nThe switch statements have explicit cases for all known agent types followed by a default return that duplicates the Claude/OpenCode case:\\n\\n```go\\nswitch agentType {\\ncase agent.AgentTypeGemini:\\n    return geminicli.SliceFromMessage(fullTranscript, startOffset)\\ncase agent.AgentTypeClaudeCode, agent.AgentTypeOpenCode, agent.AgentTypeUnknown:\\n    return transcript.SliceFromLine(fullTranscript, startOffset)\\n}\\nreturn transcript.SliceFromLine(fullTranscript, startOffset)  // Duplicate\\n```\\n\\n**Rationale:** The default case is unreachable but kept for safety. This is acceptable, but you could add a `default:` case explicitly to make intent clearer:\\n\\n```go\\ndefault:\\n    return transcript.SliceFromLine(fullTranscript, startOffset)\\n```\\n\\n### 2. [setup.go:1095-1111] Agent hooks listing could be more maintainable\\n\\nThe agent hooks listing in uninstall uses individual boolean checks. As more agents are added, this becomes verbose.\\n\\n**Suggestion:** Consider iterating over registered agents dynamically:\\n\\n```go\\nvar agentNames []string\\nfor _, name := range agent.List() {\\n    ag, err := agent.Get(name)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    if hookAgent, ok := ag.(agent.HookSupport); ok && hookAgent.AreHooksInstalled() {\\n        agentNames = append(agentNames, string(name))\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. [summarize/summarize.go:160] Rename function for consistency\\n\\n`extractGeminiToolDetail` was renamed to `extractGenericToolDetail` which is good, but the comment on line 157 still references the old behavior pattern:\\n\\n```go\\nentries = append(entries, Entry{\\n    Type:       EntryTypeTool,\\n    ToolName:   tc.Name,\\n    ToolDetail: extractGenericToolDetail(tc.Args),\\n})\\n```\\n\\nThe function itself is well-named now, no changes needed.\\n\\n### 4. [hooks_cmd.go:22-32] Import registration comment\\n\\nThe import side-effects comment is helpful. Consider adding a brief note about what the registration enables:\\n\\n```go\\n// Import agents to ensure they are registered before we iterate.\\n// Registration happens in init() functions; these imports trigger that.\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Praise\\n\\n### Well-designed ExportData mechanism\\n\\nThe `ExportData` field in `AgentSession` and `SessionContent` is an elegant solution for agents with non-file storage (OpenCode's SQLite). It preserves the agent-agnostic checkpoint architecture while allowing agents to store opaque export blobs that enable full session restoration.\\n\\n### Comprehensive test coverage\\n\\nThe new integration tests (`opencode_hooks_test.go`) provide excellent coverage of the OpenCode hook flow:\\n- Full session lifecycle (start -> turns -> end)\\n- Agent/strategy composition\\n- Rewind functionality\\n- Multi-turn scenarios\\n\\n### Clean agent interface simplification\\n\\nThe change from `HookHandler` interface to using `Agent` directly in `newAgentHooksCmd` (hook_registry.go:47) simplifies the code by removing an unnecessary interface layer.\\n\\n### Consistent error messaging in setup.go\\n\\nThe OpenCod