rceToolAssistantUUID\":\"e51e8d0d-818f-45d9-8512-66c9bb292800\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"06876bfc-bf3f-4429-8267-ac4b40954794\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-opencode\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01CHQXnCXQWRC4fhDXaf9XDa\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I understand the architecture better. Let me answer the user's question about why we capture via event stream instead of using `opencode export`.\\n\\nLooking at the code:\\n\\n1. **Event stream capture in the plugin** (`entire_plugin.ts`):\\n   - Captures `message.updated` and `message.part.updated` events in real-time\\n   - Accumulates messages in memory (`messageStore`, `partStore`)\\n   - Writes JSONL transcript + export JSON at `session.idle` (turn end)\\n\\n2. **OpenCode CLI commands used**:\\n   - `opencode import` - used during resume/rewind to import export data back into SQLite\\n   - `opencode session delete` - used before import to ensure clean reimport\\n\\nThe question is: why not just call `opencode export <session-id>` at turn-end instead of building the export data ourselves from events?\\n\\nPotential reasons:\\n1. **Timing/availability** - At `session.idle` or `session.deleted`, the OpenCode process might be shutting down. The SDK API might not be available. The plugin even has `writeTranscriptWithFallback` that falls back to in-memory stores if the API is unavailable.\\n\\n2. **Real-time capture** - Events are captured as they happen, so we always have the data even if something crashes.\\n\\n3. **Plugin isolation** - Calling `opencode export` would require shelling out to the CLI from within the plugin, which adds complexity and potential failure modes.\\n\\n4. **Session ID preservation** - We need the export data to contain the original session ID for reimport. The plugin has access to this via events.\\n\\nBut the user has a valid point - `opencode export` would be the canonical source of truth. If OpenCode changes its export format, our manual reconstruction might break.\\n\\nLet me see if there's a way to call `opencode export` and understand the tradeoffs better.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":915,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55043,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":915},\"output_tokens\":4,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYK8mEnARUFPUDYn4Vfk9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c9307553-5e46-4b91-8b43-be101efdbd42\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T10:06:52.692Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c9307553-5e46-4b91-8b43-be101efdbd42\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-opencode\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01CHQXnCXQWRC4fhDXaf9XDa\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good question. Looking at the architecture:\\n\\n**Current approach (event stream in plugin):**\\n```typescript\\n// Plugin accumulates messages in memory from events\\ncase \\\"message.updated\\\": { messageStore.set(msg.id, msg) }\\ncase \\\"message.part.updated\\\": { partStore.set(part.messageID, [...]) }\\n\\n// At turn-end, writes export JSON from memory\\ncase \\\"session.idle\\\": {\\n  await writeExportJSON(sessionID)  // builds export format manually\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Why not just call `opencode export` instead?**\\n\\n| Concern | Event Stream | `opencode export` |\\n|---------|--------------|-------------------|\\n| **Availability at shutdown** | Works even if SDK API is unavailable (falls back to memory) | May fail if OpenCode is shutting down |\\n| **Format stability** | Manual reconstruction - could break if OpenCode changes format | Canonical source of truth |\\n| **Completeness** | Only captures what we listen for | Guaranteed complete |\\n| **Latency** | Already in memory | Requires CLI invocation |\\n\\nThe plugin explicitly handles the shutdown case:\\n```typescript\\nasync function writeTranscriptWithFallback(sessionID: string): Promise<string> {\\n  try {\\n    const response = await client.session.message.list(...)  // SDK API\\n  } catch {\\n    // API unavailable (likely shutting down) — fall back to in-memory stores\\n    return writeTranscriptFromMemory(sessionID)\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**You raise a valid concern** - if OpenCode changes its export format, the manual reconstruction in `writeExportJSON()` could produce incompatible data that `opencode import` rejects.\\n\\nA more robust approach might be:\\n1. Try `opencode export <session-id>` first (canonical format)\\n2. Fall back to in-memory reconstruction only if that fails\\n\\nWant me to look into whether `opencode export` is available and could be called from the plugin or at turn-end?\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":915,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55043,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":915},\"output_tokens\":4,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYK8mEnARUFPUDYn4Vfk9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"3a63b76e-8a1c-4d3d-8f22-cdffcb00b40f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T10:07:00.139Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3a63b76e-8a1c-4d3d-8f22-cdffcb00b40f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/add-