"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD4zGWSV5ZS7PK1FJ56\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"930b19de-398c-4a52-a110-1cdb796888b0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:12.590Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"930b19de-398c-4a52-a110-1cdb796888b0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01Ru3m2t2f2w9hE7wxTY3CC2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_018yT5DKULwah9QTVHmB1wSC\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/claude-hooks-integration.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1535,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":68930,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1535},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD4zGWSV5ZS7PK1FJ56\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c9ad9aec-2952-4191-97a3-4b9531dd2cfe\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:13.129Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c9ad9aec-2952-4191-97a3-4b9531dd2cfe\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018yT5DKULwah9QTVHmB1wSC\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Entire CLI Hooks for Claude Code\\n     2→\\n     3→This document describes the hooks that Entire installs in Claude Code's `.claude/settings.json` to track AI-assisted development sessions.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Overview\\n     6→\\n     7→Entire integrates with Claude Code through six hooks that fire at different points during a session:\\n     8→\\n     9→| Hook                     | Trigger                        | Purpose                                        |\\n    10→| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- |\\n    11→| `SessionStart`           | New chat session begins        | Generate and persist Entire session ID         |\\n    12→| `UserPromptSubmit`       | User submits a prompt          | Capture pre-prompt state, check for conflicts  |\\n    13→| `Stop`                   | Claude finishes responding     | Create checkpoint with code + metadata         |\\n    14→| `PreToolUse[Task]`       | Subagent is about to start     | Capture pre-task state for diff computation    |\\n    15→| `PostToolUse[Task]`      | Subagent finishes              | Create final checkpoint for subagent work      |\\n    16→| `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]` | Subagent updates its todo list | Create incremental checkpoint if files changed |\\n    17→\\n    18→### Critical Capabilities\\n    19→\\n    20→  1. Prompt blocking - UserPromptSubmit hook needs to support returning a response to be shown in the cli session.\\n    21→    - Claude Code allows us to return a JSON response to stdout that can:\\n    22→      - Allow continuation: {\\\"continue\\\": true}\\n    23→      - Block with message: {\\\"continue\\\": false, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"Your message here\\\"}\\n    24→  2. Transcript access - Hooks receive transcript path; system needs to read it for:\\n    25→    - Extracting user prompts\\n    26→    - Extracting modified files\\n    27→    - Generating summaries\\n    28→  3. Tool use ID tracking - For subagent checkpoints, need unique tool_use_id to correlate PreToolUse and PostToolUse events\\n    29→  4. Stdin parsing - Hook input comes as JSON on stdin; agent must define its input schema\\n    30→\\n    31→## Detailed Hook Info\\n    32→\\n    33→### `SessionStart`\\n    34→\\n    35→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code session-start`\\n    36→- **Handler**: `handleSessionStart()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:907`\\n    37→\\n    38→Fires when a new chat session begins in Claude Code.\\n    39→\\n    40→**What it does:**\\n    41→\\n    42→1.  **Parse Input**: Reads session details from Claude Code's hook payload (`session_id`, `session_ref`).\\n    43→2.  **Generate Entire Session ID**: Creates a date-prefixed identifier by combining today's date with the model's session ID (e.g., `2026-01-15-ab310c99-f579-4a12-8b3c-1234567890ab`).\\n    44→3.  **Persist Session ID**: Writes the Entire session ID to `.entire/current_session`. This file is read by subsequent hooks to maintain session context across hook invocations, even if the session spans midnight (date boundary).\\n    45→\\n    46→### `UserPromptSubmit`\\n    47→\\n    48→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code user-prompt-submit`\\n    49→- **Handler**: `captureInitialState()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:248`\\n    50→\\n    51→Fires every time the user submits a prompt. Prepares the repository state tracking _before_ Claude makes any changes.\\n    52→\\n    53→**What it does:**\\n    54→\\n    55→1.  **Concurrent Session Check**:\\n    56→\\n    57→    - Queries the strategy to check if another Entire session has uncommitted checkpoints on the same HEAD commit.\\n    58→    - If a conflict is found, outputs a JSON response that blocks the prompt and shows a warning to the user.\\n    59→    - The warning includes the other session's initial prompt (if available) and a resume command.\\n    60→    - Sets `ConcurrentWarningShown` flag in session state so the user can continue on the next prompt.\\n    61→    - Once the user commits their changes (or the conflict resolves), the flag is cleared automatically.\\n    62→\\n    63→2.  **Capture Pre-Prompt State**:\\n    64→\\n    65→    - Runs `git status` to get a list of all **untracked files** in the repository.\\n    66→    - Saves this list to `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n    67→    - This baseline is compared later (in the `Stop` hook) to determine which files were newly created by Claude.\\n    68→    - Records the current transcript line count (`StepTranscriptStart`) for incremental token usage calculation.\\n    69→\\n    70→3.  **Initialize Session Strategy**:\\n    71→    - For strategies that implement `SessionInitializer`, calls `InitializeSession()`.\\n    72→    - **Manual-commit strategy**: Creates or validates the shadow branch (`entire/<HEAD-hash[:7]>`), saves session state to `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` with `BaseCommit`, `WorktreePath`, and `AgentType`.\\n    73→    - Handles shadow branch conflicts (from other worktrees) and session ID conflicts with appropriate error messages and recovery options.\\n    74→\\n    75→### `Stop`\\n    76→\\n    77→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code stop`\\n    78→- **Handler**: `commitWithMetadata()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:288`\\n    79→\\n    80→Fires when Claude finishes responding. Does **not** fire on user interrupt (Ctrl+C).\\n    81→\\n    82→**What it does:**\\n    83→\\n    84→1.  **Parse Transcript**:\\n    85→\\n    86→    - Reads the JSONL transcript from the path provided by Claude Code.\\n    87→    - Parses the full transcript. `CheckpointTranscriptStart` (or `StepTranscriptStart` from pre-prompt state) is used to detect whether new content exists since the last checkpoint.\\n    88→    - Extracts **modified files** by scanning for Write/Edit tool uses in the transcript.\\n    89→\\n    90→2.  **Extract and Save Metadata** (to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/`):\\n    91→\\n    92→    - `full.jsonl` - Copy of the complete transcript.\\n    93→    - `prompt.txt` - All user prompts from this interaction, separated by `---`.\\n    94→    - `summary.txt` - The last assistant message (used as checkpoint summary).\\n    95→    - `context.md` - Generated context file with commit message, session info, and file lists.\\n    96→\\n    97→3.  **Compute File Changes**:\\n    98→\\n    99→    - **Modified files**: Extracted from transcript (Write/Edit tool invocations).\\n   100→    - **New files**: Compare current untracked files against pre-prompt state to find files created by Claude.\\n   101→    - **Deleted files**: Query `git status` for tracked files that no longer exist.\\n   102→    - All paths are normalized relative to repo root (not cwd) to handle Claude running from subdirectories.\\n   103→\\n   104→4.  **Generate Commit Message**: Derives from the last user prompt, truncated and formatted appropriately.\\n   105→\\n   106→5.  **Calculate Token Usage**:\\n   107→\\n   108→    - Parses the transcript from `StepTranscriptStart` (captured at prompt start) to calculate tokens used in this turn.\\n   109→    - Extracts token counts from assistant messages: input tokens, cache creation/read tokens, output tokens.\\n   110→    - Deduplicates by message ID (streaming creates multiple rows per message; uses highest output_tokens).\\n   111→    - Finds spawned subagents by scanning for `agentId:` in Task tool results.\\n   112→    - Calculates subagent token usage from their transcript files (`agent-<id>.jsonl`).\\n   113→    - Aggregates into a `TokenUsage` struct with nested `SubagentTokens`.\\n   114→\\n   115→6.  **Invoke Strategy**:\\n   116→\\n   117→    - Builds a `SaveContext` with session ID, file lists, metadata paths, git author info, and token usage.\\n   118→    - Calls `strategy.SaveChanges(ctx)` to create the checkpoint.\\n   119→    - **Manual-commit**: Builds a git tree in-memory and commits to the shadow branch.\\n   120→    - **Auto-commit**: Creates a commit on the active branch with the `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer.\\n   121→    - Token usage is stored in `metadata.json` for later analysis and reporting.\\n   122→\\n   123→7.  **Update Session State**: Updates `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to track transcript position for detecting new content in future checkpoints (auto-commit strategy only).\\n   124→\\n   125→8.  **Cleanup**: Deletes the temporary `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json` file.\\n   126→\\n   127→### `PreToolUse[Task]`\\n   128→\\n   129→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code pre-task`\\n   130→- **Handler**: `handlePreTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:668`\\n   131→\\n   132→Fires just before a subagent (Task tool) begins execution. Captures the current state so that file changes can be computed when the task completes.\\n   133→\\n   134→**What it does:**\\n   135→\\n   136→1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input` from the hook payload.\\n   137→\\n   138→2.  **Extract Subagent Info**: Parses `tool_input` to get:\\n   139→\\n   140→    - `subagent_type` - The type of subagent (e.g., \\\"Explore\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\", \\\"dev\\\").\\n   141→    - `description` - The task description (e.g., \\\"Find authentication files\\\").\\n   142→\\n   143→3.  **Capture Pre-Task State**:\\n   144→\\n   145→    - Runs `git status` to get current untracked files.\\n   146→    - Saves to `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   147→    - This baseline is used by `PostToolUse[Task]` to determine which files the subagent created.\\n   148→    - **Note**: No checkpoint/commit is created at this stage. Commits are only created during task completion (`PostToolUse[Task]` or `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`) and only if there are actual file changes.\\n   149→\\n   150→### `PostToolUse[Task]`\\n   151→\\n   152→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-task`\\n   153→- **Handler**: `handlePostTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:770`\\n   154→\\n   155→Fires after a subagent finishes its work. Creates the final checkpoint for the subagent's task.\\n   156→\\n   157→**What it does:**\\n   158→\\n   159→1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `agent_id` (from `tool_response.agentId`), `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input`.\\n   160→\\n   161→2.  **Locate Subagent Transcript**:\\n   162→\\n   163→    - Constructs path: `<transcript_dir>/agent-<agent_id>.jsonl`.\\n   164→    - If the subagent transcript exists, uses it for file extraction; otherwise falls back to main transcript.\\n   165→\\n   166→3.  **Extract Modified Files**: Parses the transcript (subagent or main) to find Write/Edit tool invocations.\\n   167→\\n   168→4.  **Compute New Files**:\\n   169→\\n   170→    - Loads pre-task state from `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   171→    - Compares current untracked files against the pre-task snapshot.\\n   172→    - Files that are now untracked but weren't before = files created by the subagent.\\n   173→\\n   174→5.  **Find Checkpoint UUID**: Scans the main transcript for any checkpoint UUID associated with this `tool_use_id` (used for rewind linking).\\n   175→\\n   176→6.  **Save Final Checkpoint**:\\n   177→\\n   178→    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with all file changes, transcript paths, subagent info, and checkpoint UUID.\\n   179→    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n   180→    - Creates a commit with the subagent's file changes and metadata including the subagent transcript.\\n   181→\\n   182→7.  **Cleanup**: Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   183→\\n   184→### `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`\\n   185→\\n   186→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-todo`\\n   187→- **Handler**: `handlePostTodo()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:550`\\n   188→\\n   189→Fires whenever a subagent updates its todo list. Enables fine-grained, incremental checkpointing _during_ subagent execution.\\n   190→\\n   191→**What it does:**\\n   192→\\n   193→1.  **Subagent Context Check**:\\n   194→\\n   195→    - Looks for an active pre-task file (`.entire/tmp/pre-task-*.json`).\\n   196→    - If no pre-task file exists, this is a main agent `TodoWrite` - skip silently.\\n   197→    - This ensures incremental checkpoints only happen inside subagent Task tool invocations.\\n   198→\\n   199→2.  **Detect File Changes**:\\n   200→\\n   201→    - Calls `DetectFileChanges()` to check for modifications since the last checkpoint.\\n   202→    - Compares against git worktree status for modified, new, and deleted files.\\n   203→\\n   204→3.  **Skip if No Changes**: If no files have changed, logs a message and returns without creating a checkpoint.\\n   205→\\n   206→4.  **Extract Todo Content**:\\n   207→\\n   208→    - Parses the `tool_input.todos` array from the hook payload.\\n   209→    - Looks for the **last completed** todo item - this represents the work just finished.\\n   210→    - If no completed items (first TodoWrite), uses \\\"Planning: N todos\\\" format.\\n   211→    - This becomes the checkpoint description (e.g., \\\"Completed: Add user authentication endpoint\\\").\\n   212→\\n   213→5.  **Get Checkpoint Sequence**: Calls `GetNextCheckpointSequence()` to get an incrementing number for this task.\\n   214→\\n   215→6.  **Save Incremental Checkpoint**:\\n   216→    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with `IsIncremental: true`, sequence number, and todo content.\\n   217→    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n   218→    - Creates a small commit capturing the incremental progress.\\n   219→\\n   220→**Example sequence during a subagent Task:**\\n   221→\\n   222→```\\n   223→PreToolUse[Task]       → (no checkpoint - only captures pre-task state)\\n   224→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #1: \\\"Planning: 5 todos\\\" (if files changed)\\n   225→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #2: \\\"Completed: Create user model\\\"\\n   226→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #3: \\\"Completed: Add login endpoint\\\"\\n   227→PostToolUse[Task]      → Checkpoint #4: Final checkpoint with all changes\\n   228→```\\n   229→\\n\\n<system-reminder>\\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\\n</system-reminder>\\n\"}]},\"uuid\":\"63408142-f5e1-4bd4-a85f-a6c5602d7a9d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:13.296Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/claude-hooks-integration.md\",\"content\":\"# Entire CLI Hooks for Claude Code\\n\\nThis document describes the hooks that Entire installs in Claude Code's `.claude/settings.json` to track AI-assisted development sessions.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nEntire integrates with Claude Code through six hooks that fire at different points during a session:\\n\\n| Hook                     | Trigger                        | Purpose                                        |\\n| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- |\\n| `SessionStart`           | New chat session begins        | Generate and persist Entire session ID         |\\n| `UserPromptSubmit`       | User submits a prompt          | Capture pre-prompt state, check for conflicts  |\\n| `Stop`                   | Claude finishes responding     | Create checkpoint with code + metadata         |\\n| `PreToolUse[Task]`       | Subagent is about to start     | Capture pre-task state for diff computation    |\\n| `PostToolUse[Task]`      | Subagent finishes              | Create final checkpoint for subagent work      |\\n| `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]` | Subagent updates its todo list | Create incremental checkpoint if files changed |\\n\\n### Critical Capabilities\\n\\n  1. Prompt blocking - UserPromptSubmit hook needs to support returning a response to be shown in the cli session.\\n    - Claude Code allows us to return a JSON response to stdout that can:\\n      - Allow continuation: {\\\"continue\\\": true}\\n      - Block with message: {\\\"continue\\\": false, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"Your message here\\\"}\\n  2. Transcript access - Hooks receive transcript path; system needs to read it for:\\n    - Extracting user prompts\\n    - Extracting modified files\\n    - Generating summaries\\n  3. Tool use ID tracking - For subagent checkpoints, need unique tool_use_id to correlate PreToolUse and PostToolUse events\\n  4. Stdin parsing - Hook input comes as JSON on stdin; agent must define its input schema\\n\\n## Detailed Hook Info\\n\\n### `SessionStart`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code session-start`\\n- **Handler**: `handleSessionStart()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:907`\\n\\nFires when a new chat session begins in Claude Code.\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Parse Input**: Reads session details from Claude Code's hook payload (`session_id`, `session_ref`).\\n2.  **Generate Entire Session ID**: Creates a date-prefixed identifier by combining today's date with the model's session ID (e.g., `2026-01-15-ab310c99-f579-4a12-8b3c-1234567890ab`).\\n3.  **Persist Session ID**: Writes the Entire session ID to `.entire/current_session`. This file is read by subsequent hooks to maintain session context across hook invocations, even if the session spans midnight (date boundary).\\n\\n### `UserPromptSubmit`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code user-prompt-submit`\\n- **Handler**: `captureInitialState()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:248`\\n\\nFires every time the user submits a prompt. Prepares the repository state tracking _before_ Claude makes any changes.\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Concurrent Session Check**:\\n\\n    - Queries the strategy to check if another Entire session has uncommitted checkpoints on the same HEAD commit.\\n    - If a conflict is found, outputs a JSON response that blocks the prompt and shows a warning to the user.\\n    - The warning includes the other session's initial prompt (if available) and a resume command.\\n    - Sets `ConcurrentWarningShown` flag in session state so the user can continue on the next prompt.\\n    - Once the user commits their changes (or the conflict resolves), the flag is cleared automatically.\\n\\n2.  **Capture Pre-Prompt State**:\\n\\n    - Runs `git status` to get a list of all **untracked files** in the repository.\\n    - Saves this list to `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n    - This baseline is compared later (in the `Stop` hook) to determine which files were newly created by Claude.\\n    - Records the current transcript line count (`StepTranscriptStart`) for incremental token usage calculation.\\n\\n3.  **Initialize Session Strategy**:\\n    - For strategies that implement `SessionInitializer`, calls `InitializeSession()`.\\n    - **Manual-commit strategy**: Creates or validates the shadow branch (`entire/<HEAD-hash[:7]>`), saves session state to `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` with `BaseCommit`, `WorktreePath`, and `AgentType`.\\n    - Handles shadow branch conflicts (from other worktrees) and session ID conflicts with appropriate error messages and recovery options.\\n\\n### `Stop`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code stop`\\n- **Handler**: `commitWithMetadata()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:288`\\n\\nFires when Claude finishes responding. Does **not** fire on user interrupt (Ctrl+C).\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Parse Transcript**:\\n\\n    - Reads the JSONL transcript from the path provided by Claude Code.\\n    - Parses the full transcript. `CheckpointTranscriptStart` (or `StepTranscriptStart` from pre-prompt state) is used to detect whether new content exists since the last checkpoint.\\n    - Extracts **modified files** by scanning for Write/Edit tool uses in the transcript.\\n\\n2.  **Extract and Save Metadata** (to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/`):\\n\\n    - `full.jsonl` - Copy of the complete transcript.\\n    - `prompt.txt` - All user prompts from this interaction, separated by `---`.\\n    - `summary.txt` - The last assistant message (used as checkpoint summary).\\n    - `context.md` - Generated context file with commit message, session info, and file lists.\\n\\n3.  **Compute File Changes**:\\n\\n    - **Modified files**: Extracted from transcript (Write/Edit tool invocations).\\n    - **New files**: Compare current untracked files against pre-prompt state to find files created by Claude.\\n    - **Deleted files**: Query `git status` for tracked files that no longer exist.\\n    - All paths are normalized relative to repo root (not cwd) to handle Claude running from subdirectories.\\n\\n4.  **Generate Commit Message**: Derives from the last user prompt, truncated and formatted appropriately.\\n\\n5.  **Calculate Token Usage**:\\n\\n    - Parses the transcript from `StepTranscriptStart` (captured at prompt start) to calculate tokens used in this turn.\\n    - Extracts token counts from assistant messages: input tokens, cache creation/read tokens, output tokens.\\n    - Deduplicates by message ID (streaming creates multiple rows per message; uses highest output_tokens).\\n    - Finds spawned subagents by scanning for `agentId:` in Task tool results.\\n    - Calculates subagent token usage from their transcript files (`agent-<id>.jsonl`).\\n    - Aggregates into a `TokenUsage` struct with nested `SubagentTokens`.\\n\\n6.  **Invoke Strategy**:\\n\\n    - Builds a `SaveContext` with session ID, file lists, metadata paths, git author info, and token usage.\\n    - Calls `strategy.SaveChanges(ctx)` to create the checkpoint.\\n    - **Manual-commit**: Builds a git tree in-memory and commits to the shadow branch.\\n    - **Auto-commit**: Creates a commit on the active branch with the `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer.\\n    - Token usage is stored in `metadata.json` for later analysis and reporting.\\n\\n7.  **Update Session State**: Updates `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to track transcript position for detecting new content in future checkpoints (auto-commit strategy only).\\n\\n8.  **Cleanup**: Deletes the temporary `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json` file.\\n\\n### `PreToolUse[Task]`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code pre-task`\\n- **Handler**: `handlePreTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:668`\\n\\nFires just before a subagent (Task tool) begins execution. Captures the current state so that file changes can be computed when the task completes.\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input` from the hook payload.\\n\\n2.  **Extract Subagent Info**: Parses `tool_input` to get:\\n\\n    - `subagent_type` - The type of subagent (e.g., \\\"Explore\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\", \\\"dev\\\").\\n    - `description` - The task description (e.g., \\\"Find authentication files\\\").\\n\\n3.  **Capture Pre-Task State**:\\n\\n    - Runs `git status` to get current untracked files.\\n    - Saves to `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n    - This baseline is used by `PostToolUse[Task]` to determine which files the subagent created.\\n    - **Note**: No checkpoint/commit is created at this stage. Commits are only created during task completion (`PostToolUse[Task]` or `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`) and only if there are actual file changes.\\n\\n### `PostToolUse[Task]`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-task`\\n- **Handler**: `handlePostTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:770`\\n\\nFires after a subagent finishes its work. Creates the final checkpoint for the subagent's task.\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `agent_id` (from `tool_response.agentId`), `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input`.\\n\\n2.  **Locate Subagent Transcript**:\\n\\n    - Constructs path: `<transcript_dir>/agent-<agent_id>.jsonl`.\\n    - If the subagent transcript exists, uses it for file extraction; otherwise falls back to main transcript.\\n\\n3.  **Extract Modified Files**: Parses the transcript (subagent or main) to find Write/Edit tool invocations.\\n\\n4.  **Compute New Files**:\\n\\n    - Loads pre-task state from `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n    - Compares current untracked files against the pre-task snapshot.\\n    - Files that are now untracked but weren't before = files created by the subagent.\\n\\n5.  **Find Checkpoint UUID**: Scans the main transcript for any checkpoint UUID associated with this `tool_use_id` (used for rewind linking).\\n\\n6.  **Save Final Checkpoint**:\\n\\n    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with all file changes, transcript paths, subagent info, and checkpoint UUID.\\n    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n    - Creates a commit with the subagent's file changes and metadata including the subagent transcript.\\n\\n7.  **Cleanup**: Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n\\n### `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`\\n\\n- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-todo`\\n- **Handler**: `handlePostTodo()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:550`\\n\\nFires whenever a subagent updates its todo list. Enables fine-grained, incremental checkpointing _during_ subagent execution.\\n\\n**What it does:**\\n\\n1.  **Subagent Context Check**:\\n\\n    - Looks for an active pre-task file (`.entire/tmp/pre-task-*.json`).\\n    - If no pre-task file exists, this is a main agent `TodoWrite` - skip silently.\\n    - This ensures incremental checkpoints only happen inside subagent Task tool invocations.\\n\\n2.  **Detect File Changes**:\\n\\n    - Calls `DetectFileChanges()` to check for modifications since the last checkpoint.\\n    - Compares against git worktree status for modified, new, and deleted files.\\n\\n3.  **Skip if No Changes**: If no files have changed, logs a message and returns without creating a checkpoint.\\n\\n4.  **Extract Todo Content**:\\n\\n    - Parses the `tool_input.todos` array from the hook payload.\\n    - Looks for the **last completed** todo item - this represents the work just finished.\\n    - If no completed items (first TodoWrite), uses \\\"Planning: N todos\\\" format.\\n    - This becomes the checkpoint description (e.g., \\\"Completed: Add user authentication endpoint\\\").\\n\\n5.  **Get Checkpoint Sequence**: Calls `GetNextCheckpointSequence()` to get an incrementing number for this task.\\n\\n6.  **Save Incremental Checkpoint**:\\n    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with `IsIncremental: true`, sequence number, and todo content.\\n    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n    - Creates a small commit capturing the incremental progress.\\n\\n**Example sequence during a subagent Task:**\\n\\n```\\nPreToolUse[Task]       → (no checkpoint - only captures pre-task state)\\nPostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #1: \\\"Planning: 5 todos\\\" (if files changed)\\nPostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #2: \\\"Completed: Create user model\\\"\\nPostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #3: \\\"Completed: Add login endpoint\\\"\\nPostToolUse[Task]      → Checkpoint #4: Final checkpoint with all changes\\n```\\n\",\"numLines\":229,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":229}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"c9ad9aec-2952-4191-97a3-4b9531dd2cfe\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"63408142-f5e1-4bd4-a85f-a6c5602d7a9d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01AJfdbBwzt5ygYvJ8AHBc22\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"This is Claude-specific documentation. Let me check if there's a more general agent integration guide. I'll create a new document that serves as a checklist for implementing new agents.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4220,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":70465,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4220},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD5HJBhArXR264vwtHN\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"3dc89744-fc7c-4390-9cf2-fb2b1d17d879\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:16.610Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3dc89744-fc7c-4390-9cf2-fb2b1d17d879\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01AJfdbBwzt5ygYvJ8AHBc22\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me create a new agent integration requirements document with a checklist.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4220,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":70465,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4220},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD5HJBhArXR264vwtHN\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c5fcc7d0-0600-4c41-adbc-2d8c07073612\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:17.132Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c5fcc7d0-0600-4c41-adbc-2d8c07073612\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01AJfdbBwzt5ygYvJ8AHBc22\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Gj92Mb8HsZ1BP9qfnv68JU\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent Integration Checklist\\n\\nThis document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this when implementing support for a new agent (e.g., Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode).\\n\\n## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n\\nEntire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n\\n- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n\\n**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n\\n## Integration Checklist\\n\\n### Transcript Capture\\n\\n- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., `opencode export`, reading Claude's JSONL file) over manually reconstructing from events\\n- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\\n\\n### Why This Matters\\n\\n**Bug pattern to avoid:**\\n\\n```typescript\\n// BAD: Event-stream accumulation misses history on resumed sessions\\nconst messageStore = new Map()  // Empty on plugin load\\n\\ncase \\\"message.updated\\\":\\n  messageStore.set(msg.id, msg)  // Only captures new messages\\n\\ncase \\\"session.idle\\\":\\n  writeExport(messageStore)  // Missing historical messages!\\n```\\n\\n**Correct approach:**\\n\\n```typescript\\n// GOOD: Use agent's canonical export which includes full history\\ncase \\\"session.idle\\\":\\n  await $`agent export ${sessionID} > ${exportPath}`  // Full session from agent's DB\\n```\\n\\n### Session Storage Abstraction\\n\\n- [ ] **`WriteSession` implementation**: Agent must implement `WriteSession(AgentSession)` to restore sessions\\n- [ ] **File-based agents** (Claude, Gemini): Just write `NativeData` to `SessionRef` path\\n- [ ] **Database-backed agents** (OpenCode): Write file AND import into native storage using `ExportData`\\n- [ ] **Format compatibility**: Export data format must be compatible with agent's import command\\n\\n### Hook Events\\n\\n- [ ] **turn-start**: Fire when user submits a prompt (for pre-prompt state capture)\\n- [ ] **turn-end**: Fire when agent finishes responding (for checkpoint creation)\\n- [ ] **session-start**: Fire when a new session begins\\n- [ ] **session-end**: Fire when session is explicitly ended (optional but recommended)\\n\\n### Rewind/Resume Support\\n\\n- [ ] **Rewind restores full state**: After rewind, agent can continue from that point with full context\\n- [ ] **Resume command**: `FormatResumeCommand()` returns the CLI command to resume a session\\n- [ ] **Session ID preservation**: Restored sessions maintain original session ID where possible\\n\\n### Testing\\n\\n- [ ] **New session**: Create session, multiple turns, verify full transcript at each checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session**: Resume existing session, add turns, verify checkpoint includes historical messages\\n- [ ] **Rewind**: Rewind to earlier checkpoint, verify agent can continue from that state\\n- [ ] **Agent shutdown**: Verify graceful handling if agent exits during checkpoint\\n\\n## Agent-Specific Notes\\n\\n### Claude Code\\n- Transcript: JSONL file on disk, always complete\\n- Storage: File-based, `WriteSession` just writes file\\n- Resume: `claude --resume <session-id>`\\n\\n### Gemini CLI\\n- Transcript: JSON file on disk, always complete\\n- Storage: File-based, `WriteSession` just writes file\\n- Resume: `gemini --session <session-id>`\\n\\n### OpenCode\\n- Transcript: SQLite database (not directly accessible)\\n- Storage: Database-backed, `WriteSession` must import via `opencode import`\\n- Export: Use `opencode export <session-id>` for canonical format\\n- Resume: `opencode -s <session-id>`\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4220,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":70465,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4220},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD5HJBhArXR264vwtHN\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"d2f35df1-b9da-45ad-9bc1-3120df83e078\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:41.800Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"d2f35df1-b9da-45ad-9bc1-3120df83e078\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"ac9f5322-da07-49f7-aa81-0df85c0caf27\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"804279638ad5a715@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-02-20T10:06:27.584Z\"},\"docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"c8f6046c7e695166@v1\",\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:41.931Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:04.173Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d2f35df1-b9da-45ad-9bc1-3120df83e078\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Gj92Mb8HsZ1BP9qfnv68JU\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"d53ffeb9-06ff-40f2-b62a-ac52418083ef\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:41.928Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"create\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent Integration Checklist\\n\\nThis document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this when implementing support for a new agent (e.g., Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode).\\n\\n## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n\\nEntire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n\\n- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n\\n**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n\\n## Integration Checklist\\n\\n### Transcript Capture\\n\\n- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., `opencode export`, reading Claude's JSONL file) over manually reconstructing from events\\n- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\\n\\n### Why This Matters\\n\\n**Bug pattern to avoid:**\\n\\n```typescript\\n// BAD: Event-stream accumulation misses history on resumed sessions\\nconst messageStore = new Map()  // Empty on plugin load\\n\\ncase \\\"message.updated\\\":\\n  messageStore.set(msg.id, msg)  // Only captures new messages\\n\\ncase \\\"session.idle\\\":\\n  writeExport(messageStore)  // Missing historical messages!\\n```\\n\\n**Correct approach:**\\n\\n```typescript\\n// GOOD: Use agent's canonical export which includes full history\\ncase \\\"session.idle\\\":\\n  await $`agent export ${sessionID} > ${exportPath}`  // Full session from agent's DB\\n```\\n\\n### Session Storage Abstraction\\n\\n- [ ] **`WriteSession` implementation**: Agent must implement `WriteSession(AgentSession)` to restore sessions\\n- [ ] **File-based agents** (Claude, Gemini): Just write `NativeData` to `SessionRef` path\\n- [ ] **Database-backed agents** (OpenCode): Write file AND import into native storage using `ExportData`\\n- [ ] **Format compatibility**: Export data format must be compatible with agent's import command\\n\\n### Hook Events\\n\\n- [ ] **turn-start**: Fire when user submits a prompt (for pre-prompt state capture)\\n- [ ] **turn-end**: Fire when agent finishes responding (for checkpoint creation)\\n- [ ] **session-start**: Fire when a new session begins\\n- [ ] **session-end**: Fire when session is explicitly ended (optional but recommended)\\n\\n### Rewind/Resume Support\\n\\n- [ ] **Rewind restores full state**: After rewind, agent can continue from that point with full context\\n- [ ] **Resume command**: `FormatResumeCommand()` returns the CLI command to resume a session\\n- [ ] **Session ID preservation**: Restored sessions maintain original session ID where possible\\n\\n### Testing\\n\\n- [ ] **New session**: Create session, multiple turns, verify full transcript at each checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session**: Resume existing session, add turns, verify checkpoint includes historical messages\\n- [ ] **Rewind**: Rewind to earlier checkpoint, verify agent can continue from that state\\n- [ ] **Agent shutdown**: Verify graceful handling if agent exits during checkpoint\\n\\n## Agent-Specific Notes\\n\\n### Claude Code\\n- Transcript: JSONL file on disk, always complete\\n- Storage: File-based, `WriteSession` just writes file\\n- Resume: `claude --resume <session-id>`\\n\\n### Gemini CLI\\n- Transcript: JSON file on disk, always complete\\n- Storage: File-based, `WriteSession` just writes file\\n- Resume: `gemini --session <session-id>`\\n\\n### OpenCode\\n- Transcript: SQLite database (not directly accessible)\\n- Storage: Database-backed, `WriteSession` must import via `opencode import`\\n- Export: Use `opencode export <session-id>` for canonical format\\n- Resume: `opencode -s <session-id>`\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[],\"originalFile\":null},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"d2f35df1-b9da-45ad-9bc1-3120df83e078\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d53ffeb9-06ff-40f2-b62a-ac52418083ef\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/small-rewind-refactor\",\"slug\":\"calm-brewing-cerf\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01PRRA2uSprUYVzsrxySpKZ8\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Good, I've created the checklist document. Let me also update the CLAUDE.md to reference this new document in the agent section.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1184,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":74685,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1184},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKD7PoR6NLsqHb7TQK3k\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"b9f10978-e63a-43e2-9edd-abe5c267b492\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T11:03:44.968Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b9f10978-e63a-43e2-9edd-abe5c267b492\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a8533fc6-4167-49d5-9143-32f1d83dd315\",\"versio